<HEADLINE> Beijing Imports German Condensing TG Units </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 29 (Xinhua) -- The Beijing No.1 Thermal Power
plant has imported two sets of Double Extraction Condensing TG
Units valued at 550 million US dollars from Germany for its
technical transformation.
</P>
<P>
The import contract for the units was signed here today in the
Great Hall of the People by the China National Technical Import &AMP;
Export Corporation, North China Power Group and the China National
Tendering Center for Machinery &AMP; Electrical Equipment on the one
side and the German ABB Kraftwerke AG on the other.
</P>
<P>
ABB won the contract to supply the units through international
tendering.
</P>
<P>
The import is one of the major projects for technical
transformation of the capital's large and medium-sized
enterprises. The completion of the project by the end of 1998 is
expected to ensure a safe and stable supply of heat and
electricity in east Beijing. 
</P>
</TEXT>
