<HEADLINE> Two Dropped From HK Delegation For East Asian Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 29 (Xinhua) -- Two gymnasts would probably be
dropped from the Hong Kong delegation for the 2nd East Asian Games
slated for May 10-19 in Pusan, South Korea, it was announced here
on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Doctors of the delegation advised that the names of the two be
erased from the delegation roaster. But the Hong Kong Gymnastic
Association wish to keep them in the delegation and they would
make a last-minute effort on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
But officials of the Hong Kong Amateur Sports Federation and
Olympic Committee (HKASF&AMP;OC) said that it was up to the
Association to make the final decision.
</P>
<P>
With the two erased off the list, the Hong Kong squad would
shrink to 49 athletes and 12 officials.
</P>
<P>
The Pusan Games will be the last comprehensive sporting event
Hong Kong athletes to participate before the handover at the
midnight on June 30 this year.
</P>
<P>
From July 1 on, athletes of Hong Kong, which will be called the
 Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR), will compete in
international events under the name of "Hong Kong, China", as
stipulated by the Basic Law concerning the SAR.
</P>
<P>
In Pusan, Hong Kong athletes will compete in six medal sports,
namely athletics, gymnastics, badminton, judo, swimming and
diving, and Wushu and demonstration events of rowing and bowling.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong brought about one gold, two silver and eight bronze
medals from the same eight sports at the inaugural East Asian
Games in 1993 in Shanghai. But two of the events have now become
exhibition events.
</P>
<P>
It is believed that Hong Kong athletes are hopeful of winning
medals in Wushu, athletics, Bowling and rowing.
</P>
<P>
"Now it's up to you," said HKASF&AMP;OC President A. de O. Sales at
a reception here on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The delegation members leave Hong Kong for South Korea in four
groups, with the first one set to leave here on May 7. 
</P>
</TEXT>
