<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, April 29 (Xinhua) -- The Confederation of Zimbabwe
Industries (CZI) has blamed government bureaucracy for fuelling
the country's economic woes in the face of an increasingly
competitive global economic environment.
</P>
<P>
CZI president Jonee Blanchfield today said at the
organisation's annual general meeting that delays by the
govedrnment on key national issues like the new tariff regime had
resulted in the country losing its competitive edge in a region
that continued to be dominated by South Africa.
</P>
<P>
