<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe to Recover Iron, Steel Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, April 29 (Xinhua) -- At least 200 million U.S. dollars
will be required to turn around the troubled Zimbabwe Iron and
Steel Company (ZISCO) in a rehabilitation programme the
government hopes to complete by the end of next year.
</P>
<P>
Industry and Commerce Minister Nathan Shamuyarira today said
the rehabilitation had to precede the eventual privatisation as
no investor would buy the parastatal in its present state.
</P>
<P>
ZISCO is operating at 30 percent of capacity because a major
blast furnace, number four, was shut down for relining over two
years ago and the work is being done by a Chinese company.
</P>
<P>
The government had clung to the ailing steel giant for years
because of its importance in providing materials to the
manufacturing sector.
</P>
<P>
The minister said, "it underpins the production in all other
manufacturing industries, for the nation it is very important
that we have a thriving steel industry." 
</P>
</TEXT>
