<HEADLINE> Iranian FM to Visit Lebanon Next Week </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, April 29 (Xinhua) -- Iran's Foreign Minister Ali Akbar
Velayati will visit Lebanon next week to deliver a "written
message" to Lebanese President Elias Hrawi from his Iranian
counterpart Akbar Hashemi Rafsanjani, an Iranian diplomat said
here today.
</P>
<P>
Iranian Ambassador to Lebanon Hamaion Alizadah said that
Velayati will be here in the middle of the next week, but noted
that "more coordination" is needed in order to define the date.
</P>
<P>
Alizadah held talks with Thafer Hassan, secretary general of
the Lebanese Foreign Ministry, in the latter's office. The
Iranian envoy said that the talks dealt with bilateral relations
and developments in the region in addition to Velayati's visit to
Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
A visit by Lebanese Prime Minister Rafik Hariri to Tehran "in
the next months" was also discussed, the Iranian diplomat told
reporters at the end of the meeting.
</P>
<P>
Answering a question on why Iran did not supply missiles to
the Lebanese Hezbollah, or Party of God, in order to shoot down
Israeli warplanes in south Lebanon, Alizadah stressed that the
key for the victory of the resistance was the "resolution" rather
than the weapon.
</P>
<P>
The Shiite fundamentalist Hezbollah, which is backed by Iran,
spearheads a guerrilla warfare in south Lebanon in order to oust
Israeli occupation forces from the Lebanese land.
</P>
<P>
"The resistance of the Lebanese people agaisnt the Zionist
enemy in south Lebanon is not with the weapon, we can say that
there is not a military balance between the resistance and the
Zionist enemy," the Iranian ambassador noted.
</P>
<P>
"We hope that all the world and all countries which love the
freedom help Lebanon and support it in all fields," he
said. 
</P>
