<HEADLINE> Portuguese President Meets Afonso Dhlakama </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, April 29 (Xinhua) -- Portuguese President Jorge
Sampaio who is visiting Mozambique met with Afonso Dhlakama,
leader of the biggest opposition party the Mozambique National
Resistance (RENAMO) here this morning and exchanged views on
matters of common concern, especially local elections to be
held this November.
</P>
<P>
According to a Mozambican News Agency report, Afonso Dhlakama
during the meeting asked Portugal to increase investment in
Mozambique, saying that the investment should involve
infrastructure and professional training. However, so far,
Portugal's investments are mainly concentrated in banking and
other monetary institutions.
</P>
<P>
Portuguese have the most shares of the major banks in
Mozambique such as the Commercial Bank of Mozambique (BCM) and
the International Bank of Mozambique (BIM), said the report.
</P>
<P>
Of the 1.5 billion U.S. dollars foreign capital that has so
far flown into Mozambique, 26 percent is from Portugal.
</P>
<P>
Dhlakama also hoped that Portugal will provide funds for the
coming election in Mozambique.
</P>
<P>
President Jorge Sampaio today also met Mozambican parliament
speaker Eduardo Mulembwe and leaders of the three major parties
-- the ruling party the Front of Liberation of Mozambique
(FRELIMO Party), the National Resistance of Mozambique (RENAMO),
and the Democratic Union in the parliament.
</P>
<P>
The Portuguese president arrived in Maputo Monday and will
stay here in Mozambique for 6 days. 
</P>
