<HEADLINE> Fourth OAU/ICRC Seminar on International </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, April 29 (Xinhua) -- A two-day seminar organized
by the Organization of African Unity (OAU) and the International
Committee of the Red Cross (ICRC) on the implementation of the
international humanitarian law was opened here today.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the opening ceremony, Ahmed Haggag, the OAU Assistant
Secretary General, said, the full and effective implementation of
international humanitarian law would not only save lives but also
ameliorate some of the catastrophic consequences of armed conflicts.
</P>
<P>
He recalled the humanitarian tragedy that occurred during the
Rwandan civil war and said the smooth functioning of the interna-
tional tribunal for Rwanda is most essential for the success of
efforts at the healing of society, reconciliation and nation building
in Rwanda.
</P>
<P>
Judge Laity Kama, President of the International Criminal
Tribunal for Rwanda in Arusha, Judge Richard Goldstone, former Chief
Prosecutor of the tribunals for ex-Yugoslavia and Arusha, as well as
Professor Ahmed Mahiou, President of the UN International Law
Commission, and Professor Deny Segui, Rapporteur of the Human
Rights Commission on Rwanda, will address at the seminar.
