<HEADLINE> Over 10,000 Former Angolan Rebels Enroled in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, April 29 (Xinhua) -- A total of 10,904 former rebels
of the National Union for the Total Independence of Angola
(UNITA) have so far been enroled in the unified army.
</P>
<P>
According to statistics by the United Nations Angola
Verification Mission, 317 of them are officers.
</P>
<P>
Under the Lusaka Peace Accord signed by the warring parties of
Angola in 1994, 26,300 former UNITA rebels should be enroled in
the unified army. However, the Joint Commission Overseeing the
Peace Process in Angola has recently decided to reduce the
figure to 19,813.
</P>
<P>
By now, 19,099 former UNITA men have been selected for the
unified army.
</P>
<P>
The repatriation of former UNITA rebels is going on in the
southern African nation and 3,980 former rebels have been
demobilized and repatriated up to date, according to the UNAVEM.
