<HEADLINE> East African Lawmakers Urged to Facilitate </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, April 29 (Xinhua) -- The presidents of Kenya,
Tanzania and Uganda today directed the East African Cooperation
(EAC) to involve the region's legislators in the development of
the regional grouping.
</P>
<P>
Kenyan President Daniel Arap Moi, Ugandan President Yoweri
Museveni and Tanzanian President Benjamin Mkapa in a communique
issued in Arusha, northern Tanzania, today praised the
recommendation of the speakers of east African national
assemblies.
</P>
<P>
They welcomed the idea of parliamentarians familiarizing
themselves and getting involved in the affairs of the EAC,
directing the permanent tripartite commission to consult on the
modalities to involve them in development.
</P>
<P>
The heads of state, who were in Arusha for a one-day summit
of the EAC, noted with appreciation the progress made by the
commission in implementing cooperation programs and activities
since it was launched last year.
</P>
<P>
So far, progress has been made in the harmonization
of fiscal and monetary policies as exemplified by convertibility
of the three east African currencies.
</P>
<P>
There has also been promotion of trade, investment and the
growth of the private sector by establishment of the East African
Business Council, an apex body comprising all national private
sector organizations in the region.
</P>
<P>
Over the year, mechanisms for enhancing trade among the three
member states has been put up and also the initiation of
infrastructure-related programs and projects designed to promote
closer linkages of the member countries.
</P>
<P>
In the communique, the three men also directed the
commission to embark on negotiations for the upgrading of the
pact establishing the permanent tripartite commission for
cooperation to the status of a treaty.
</P>
<P>
The three leaders reaffirmed their commitment to
strengthening and deepening cooperation in agreed fields with a
view to bringing equitable development among the members.
</P>
<P>
They also committed themselves to promoting sustainable
utilization of the region's natural resources and effective
protection of the environment.
</P>
<P>
The presidents further reaffirmed their commitment to
enhancing the role of women in development and promoting peace,
security and good neighborliness in the region.
</P>
<P>
The presidents launched the EAC development strategy
(1997-2000) which lays the foundation for the translation of the
vision of the cooperation into a comprehensive action plan.
</P>
<P>
They also launched the east African passport and the east
African flag. enditem


