<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nigerian Doctor Defies Armed Robbers, Kills 2 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, April 29 (Xinhua) -- A doctor here showed rare courage
at the weekend when he defied six armed robbers and killed two of
them in a fierce shoot-out, the News Agency of Nigeria reported
today.
</P>
<P>
The robbers carrying locally made handguns, daggers and other
weapons, forced into the compound in Isolo area where the doctor
lives and ordered him to open his door.
</P>
<P>
Instead of obeying the robbers' orders, the doctor brought out
his double-barrel gun and fired at the robbers, killing two
instantly while the rest fled.
</P>
<P>
The robbers had earlier attacked a tenant in the same compound
and took away 7,000 Naira (about 80 U.S. Dollars), the report
said.
</P>
<P>
The police later found 15 shell cartridges and the bodies of
the two dead robbers at the scene, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The police also found that the doctor's house was severely
damaged with windows, doors and walls shattered in the gunfire.
</P>
<P>
A police spokesman has commended the doctor for his courage,
lamenting that the "lack of response by law-abiding citizens is
what gives armed gangs to attack with impunity", the report said.
</P>
<P>
The doctor was not identified by the report. 
</P>
</TEXT>
