<HEADLINE> Yeltsin Condemns Attack Against Tajik President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 30 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin
today condemned a terrorist action aimed at assassinating Tajik
President Emomali Rakhmonov, the Itar-Tass news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
"I strongly condemn this criminal act behind which, no doubt,
are the opponents of the policy of national reconciliation
conducted by the Tajik leadership," Yeltsin said in a message to
Rakhmonov.
</P>
<P>
