<HEADLINE> 4 Village Guards Killed in Southeastern Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, April 30 (Xinhua) -- Four village guards were killed
and four others wounded in an armed clash with the outlawed
Kurdish Workers' Party (PKK) rebels in Hakkari province, the
semi-official Anatolia News Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
It said that a group of PKK militants launched armed attacks
against the village guards late Tuesday night in Cinarli village
of Cukurca town, triggering the clash. Two PKK rebels were also
killed in the conflict.
</P>
<P>
The wounded village guards were taken by helicopter to
Hakkari State Hospital this morning for treatment, said the
agency.
</P>
<P>
On Monday, the PKK shot dead five village guards in Bagozu
village in Dargecit town of Mardin province bordering
neighboring Syria.
</P>
<P>
The PKK has been fighting a separatist war in southeastern
Turkey for autonomy since August 1984, in which over 21,000
people, including PKK rebels, civilians and government troops
were killed. 
</P>
