<HEADLINE> Arab Countries Plan Closer Anti-crime </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TUNIS, April 30 (Xinhua) -- The sixth conference of Arab
criminal investigation agencies concluded here today with the
recommendation of a stepped-up cooperation among Arab states in
the fight against crime.
</P>
<P>
A conference communique recommended the expansion of training
of criminal investigation officers and the establishment of an
Arab criminal statistics network.
</P>
<P>
The conference called for the intensification of efforts to
eradicate quackery and swindlers who are behind various crimes
such as swindling, trickery and rape.
</P>
<P>
The recommendations have been referred to the secretariat of
the Arab Interior Ministers Council to have them submitted to the
upcoming session of Arab Interior Minister due to take place early
next year.
</P>
<P>
The three-day conference was attended by chiefs of criminal
investigation agencies in the member states as well as
representative of the League of Arab States and the Nayef Academy
of criminal sciences.
</P>
<P>
The conference of chiefs of criminal investigation officers
periodically convenes within the framework of the secretariat of
the Arab Interior Ministers Council. 
</P>
</TEXT>
