<HEADLINE> Tajik President Condemns Terrorist Attack </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 30 (Xinhua) -- The wounded Tajik President,
Emomali Rakhmonov, strongly condemned the terrorist attack in
northern Tajikistan early today which killed two people and
injured 49, including the president.
</P>
<P>
The terrorist action "was conducted by some individuals and
agent provocateurs who will be punished," said Rakhmonov, several
hours after the grenade attack, a plot to assassinate him, in the
town of Khudjand, Itar-Tass news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Rakhmonov, 44, was wounded in the leg, and his life was not in
danger, his press secretary Zafar Saidov said.
</P>
<P>
Speaking in the regional theater of Khudjand, the president
expressed deep sorrow for the two dead -- a 17-year-old student
and a woman teacher at the local university.
</P>
<P>
The attack occurred at 10:30 a.m. local time (0530 GMT) when a
lone assailant hurled a grenade after Rakhmonov had got out of his
car and was heading to a theater for celebrations marking the 65th
anniversary of the Khudjand University.
</P>
<P>
The grenade landed near the president and other local leaders
when they were only a few steps from the entrance to the theater,
reports said.
</P>
<P>
Others among the other 48 wounded included Leninabad district
chief Kasim Kasimov, his deputy Akil Akilov, and chief of the
Tajik Customs Committee Yakubdjon Saidov.
</P>
<P>
The attacker, identified as Firdavs Dustboboyev, 26, was
detained immediately after the incident. 
</P>
</TEXT>
