<HEADLINE> Guangzhou Trade Fair For Foreign-Funded Enterprises Closes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, April 30 (Xinhua) -- Deals worth nearly 60 million
US dollars were struck during the Eighth Trade Fair for
Foreign-Funded Enterprises in China in this capital city of south
China's Guangdong Province.
</P>
<P>
The trade fair, specially organized for foreign-funded ventures
in China, closed today.
</P>
<P>
About 4,500 overseas businessmen attended.
</P>
<P>
Nearly all the commodities on show during the fair were light
industrial products such as washing machines, toys, water boilers,
foodstuffs and handicrafts.  
</P>
</TEXT>
