<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Deposits, Loans, Advances Down in March </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 30 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's deposits, loans and
advances decreased in March, partly due to the high base of
comparison in February, according to figures published today by
the Hong Kong Monetary Authority (HKMA).
</P>
<P>
Total deposits fell by 1.3 percent in March, reversing the rise
of 2.8 percent in February. Both HK dollar deposits and foreign
currency deposits dropped, by 2.2 percent and 0.1 percent
respectively.
</P>
<P>
The decline in HK dollar deposits was across-the-board,
including demand, savings and time deposits.
</P>
<P>
On the other hand, total loans and advances fell by 2.5 percent
in March, reversing the rise of 2.6 percent in February.
</P>
<P>
Analyzed by currency, both HK dollar loans and foreign currency
loans fell during the month, by 1.4 percent and 3.2 percent
respectively.
</P>
<P>
As the decline in HK dollar loans was more moderate than that
of HK dollar deposits, the currency's loan-to-deposit ratio edged
up to 109.1 percent at the end of March, from 108.2 percent at the
end of February.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
