<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 32 New Building Plans Approved in Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 30 (Xinhua) -- The Building Department
approved 32 building plans in March with six on Hong Kong Island,
14 in Kowloon and 12 in the New Territories.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman of the department said that the approved plans
covered 14 for apartment and commercial developments, five for
commercial developments, nine for factory and industrial
developments, and four for community services developments.
</P>
<P>
He said that the declared cost of the new buildings completed
in the month totaled about 1.424 billion HK dollars (183.74
million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
He said that consent was given during the month for work to
start on 43 building projects, which would provide 106,969 square
meters of usable domestic floor area and 170,587 square meters of
usable non-domestic floor area on completion.
</P>
<P>
The department also issued 45 Occupation Permits with six on
Hong Kong island, five in Kowloon and 34 in the New Territories.
</P>
<P>
Of the building certified for occupation in March, the usable
floor area for domestic and non-domestic uses was 84,911 square
meters and 91,762 square meters respectively.  
</P>
</TEXT>
