<DOCNO> XIE19970430.0089 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK, Macao Delegations Celebrate Labor Day in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 30 (Xinhua) -- The All-China Federation of Trade
Unions (ACFTU) held a gathering in the Great Hall of the People
here today in honor of delegates from its Hong Kong and Macao
counterparts.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Dinghua, vice-president and member of the Secretariat of
the ACFTU, expressed a welcome and addressed a festival message to
the visitors.
</P>
<P>
He said that 62 days remain before China resumes the exercise
of its sovereignty over Hong Kong, which signals a significant
step toward China's reunification. The event also inspires all the
Chinese people, including the Hong Kong compatriots, he added.
</P>
<P>
Zhang noted that the Hong Kong Federation of Trade Unions and
other organizations in the region have contributed a great deal to
safeguarding the legitimate rights and interests of the Hong Kong
workers.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, they also play an important role in the promotion of
the Basic Law and the "one country, two systems" principle, he
said.
</P>
<P>
Zhang pledged that after the return of Hong Kong, his
federation will extend more exchanges and cooperation with its
Hong Kong and Macao counterparts, under the "one country, two
systems" principle and the Basic Law.
</P>
<P>
Representatives from Hong Kong and Macao also spoke at the
gathering, saying that they will continue to work for the smooth
transition of Hong Kong and Macao.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
