<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> CPC Official Meets ROK Guests </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 30 (Xinhua) -- A senior official of the
Communist Party of China (CPC) said here today that the CPC is
willing to reinforce its relations with the New Korea Party (NKP),
the ruling party of the Republic of Korea (ROK), in a bid to
further the good-neighborly relations between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Hu Jintao, a standing committee member of the Political Bureau
of the CPC Central Committee and a member of the Secretariat of
the CPC Central Committee, met with an NKP delegation here today.
</P>
<P>
Over the past five years since China and the ROK established
diplomatic relations, bilateral ties have witnessed smooth
progress, and the two nations' co-operation in various fields has
reaped encouraging results, Hu said.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the establishment of long-term good-neighborly
relations between the two countries accords with the fundamental
interests of the two nations, and benefits peace and stability on
the Korean peninsula and even Asia as a whole.
</P>
<P>
The CPC is willing to make its relations with the NKP closer,
based on the principles of independence, equality, mutual-respect
and non-interference in each other's internal affairs, in an
effort to promote the co-operative ties between the two countries,
he said.
</P>
<P>
The NKP delegation is led by Lee Sai Ji, a former member of
the NKP's Party Affairs Committee, member of the ROK National
Assembly and ROK National Assembly secretary-general in charge of
culture, sports and news.
</P>
<P>
The ROK pays close attention to China's development, and the NKP,
while emphasizing its friendly co-operation with the CPC, is
willing to contribute more to the promotion of friendship and
coordination between the two countries, said Lee.
</P>
<P>
The delegation arrived here earlier today at the invitation of
the CPC.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
