<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Welcomes Peace Agreement In Sudan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 30 (Xinhua) -- China welcomes and supports the
peace agreement signed between the Sudanese government and four
southern opposition factions recently, a Chinese Foreign Ministry
spokesman said here today.
</P>
<P>
Answering a question about China's response to the signing of
the peace agreement on April 21, ministry spokesman Cui Tiankai
said that the signing of the peace agreement is in conformity with
the Sudanese people's desire for peace.
</P>
<P>
"China expresses its welcome and support for this move," he said.
</P>
<P>
He explained that China believes that the implementation of the
peace agreement will help promote a peaceful solution to the issue
of southern Sudan and benefit the national solidarity and
stability of that country. It will also enable the Sudanese people
to expand construction in a peaceful environment and allow its
people to enjoy happy and contented lives, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
