<HEADLINE> Lewis-Akinwande WBC Title Fight Set on July 12 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 30 (Xinhua) -- Lennox Lewis will defense his
first WBC heavyweight title against unbeaten Henry Akinwande on
July 12 in Atlantic City.
</P>
<P>
Lewis' manager Frank Maloney and Akinwande's promoter Don King
decided changed the site from London to New Jersey after lengthy
negotiations.
</P>
<P>
Frank Maloney said Wednesday that Lewis is expected to earn 5.2
million U.S. dollars from the fight.
</P>
<P>
Lewis, 30-1, won the title February 7 in Las Vegas when the
referee stopped the fight after a seemingly confused Oliver McCall
threw only two punches in the fourth round and one in the
fifth. Lewis' only previous loss was to McCall.
</P>
<P>
Akinwande, who has relinquished his WBO title to fight Lewis,
has 32 wins, no losses and one draw. He was ranked fourth by the
WBC behind Lewis, McCall and Mike Tyson.
</P>
<P>
Akinwande was awarded the mandatory challenge because he was
the highest available contender since Tyson is to fight WBA
champion Evander Holyfield in a rematch June 28. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
