<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sino-Portuguese Coordinating Group Established </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 30 (Xinhua) -- The first meeting of the
Sino-Portuguese coordinating group on Macao-Mainland large capital
construction projects was held here today.
</P>
<P>
Xie Houhe, group leader of the Chinese side, said the
convocation of the meeting means the formal establishment of the
group responsible to coordinate large-scale capital construction
between Macao and China's inland areas.
</P>
<P>
If necessary, the group can exchange views on other important
issues regarding economic relations between Macao and the inland
areas.
</P>
<P>
Both Macao and the inland areas are close in economic ties and
have advantages in their economic growth. They are now drawing up
plans and engaged in infrastructure construction in order to
improve their environment for investment.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese and Portuguese governments decided to set up the
group through friendly consultations and earnest preparations for
the purpose of avoiding overlapping construction and reducing the
waste of resources.
</P>
<P>
Leonel Miranda is a group leader of the Portuguese side.
</P>
<P>
Xie said at today's meeting that during the past ten years
since China and Portugal signed the Joint Declaration on the
Question of Macao in April 1987, Macao's society has been stable
and its economy has been growing. One of the main reasons is that
the two countries have cooperated well.
</P>
<P>
The establishment of the group represents another example of
Sino-Portuguese friendly cooperation, which will surely exert a
far-reaching influence on their economic development, he said.
</P>
<P>
Xie said the Chinese side is closely following Macao's economic
growth. In the past, "we rendered assistance to Macao in many
aspects including the construction of the Macao International
Airport. In the future we will continue to give necessary
assistance and help to it within our ability".
</P>
<P>
After the meeting, the two sides issued a press communique.
</P>
</TEXT>
