<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Second Czech Minister Resigns </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, April 30 (Xinhua) -- Czech Regional Development and
Housing Minister Jaromir Schneider says he will resign.
</P>
<P>
Schneider, who voiced his decision at a news conference on
Tuesday, would become the second cabinet member of Prime Minister
Vaclav Klaus's coalition government to resign in five months.
</P>
<P>
Jan Kalvoda, a former deputy prime minister and justice
minister, resigned last December.
</P>
<P>
Schneider, of the Christian Democratic Union-People's Party,
made the decision under pressure from within his party which
accuses him of not doing his best in his work.
</P>
<P>
He was blamed particularly for not properly implementing the
intentions of the party in housing construction.
</P>
<P>
Klaus said he would accept the resignation of Schneider, and a
new minister would be decided on in two weeks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
