<HEADLINE> Forum Marks 50th Birthday of Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 30 (Xinhua) -- An academic forum was held here
today to mark the 50th anniversary of the founding of the Inner
Mongolia Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
Inner Mongolia, China's first provincial-level autonomous
region, was set up on May 1, 1947. Over the past 50 years it has
scored great achievements in economy, culture, education and
public health, the participants agreed.
</P>
<P>
The Region has contrived a series of effective measures and
ways to promote the autonomy of minority nationalities, foster
cadres from among ethnic minorities, advance democratic reforms in
pastoral areas and develop animal husbandry, they pointed out.
</P>
<P>
Inner Mongolia has thus provided valuable experience for the
establishment and development of the other autonomous areas of
different ethnic groups in China, the forum participants said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
