<HEADLINE> Singaporean Prime Minister in Dalian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, April 30 (Xinhua) -- Singaporean Prime Minister Goh
Chok Tong and his party met yesterday with officials in the port
city of Dalian in northeast China.
</P>
<P>
Dalian Mayor Bo Xilai met with Goh Chok Tong and briefed him on
the city's situation. The Singaporean prime minister said that
Dalian has witnessed a rapid economic growth and stressed economic
cooperation with foreign countries.
</P>
<P>
Goh said he hopes that the Singaporean business people
accompanying him on his China trip will find more opportunities
here.
</P>
<P>
Governor of northeast China's Liaoning province Wen Shizhen
also met with Goh, saying the fact that Prime Minister Goh took
time to visit Dalian from his tight schedule demonstrates the
importance placed by Singapore to advancing its cooperation with
the province and the city.
</P>
<P>
Although Liaoning and Singapore have had successful cooperation
in recent years, Wen said, there is still potential yet to be
tapped.
</P>
<P>
Goh said that the Singaporean government will encourage more
Singaporean businesses to invest in Liaoning and Dalian.
</P>
<P>
During Goh's stay here, a memo of understanding on the training
of the city's managerial personnel by Singapore's Trade
Development Board was signed here on Tuesday afternoon. 
</P>
</TEXT>
