<HEADLINE> Improvement of Legal System in Ethnic Minority Areas Urged </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 30 (Xinhua) -- A senior Chinese legislator said
that the enactment and implementation of rules on regional
autonomy in ethnic minority areas should be improved to promote
social, economic, and cultural development in these areas.
</P>
<P>
Buhe, vice-chairman of the Standing Committee of the Eighth
National People's Congress (NPC), made the remark at a meeting
today to mark the 50th anniversary of the founding of the Inner
Mongolia Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region, set up on May 1, 1947, was
the the first provincial-level autonomous region in the country.
</P>
<P>
To date, China has set up five provincial-level autonomous
regions, 30 autonomous prefectures, and 121 autonomous counties
(or banners). Areas that are under ethnic autonomy accounts for
more than 60 percent of the territory, and covers 44 out of
China's 55 ethnic minorities.
</P>
<P>
Today's meeting was co-organized by the Chinese Society on
Nationality Studies, the Research Center on Ethnic Issues under
the State Nationalities Affairs Commission, and the Inner Mongolia
Autonomous Region. Ismail Amet, State Councilor and director of
the State Nationalities Affairs Commission attended the meeting.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
