<HEADLINE> Sino-Japanese Agriculture Symposium </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 30 (Xinhua) -- Chinese agricultural experts are
hosting a Sino-Japanese symposium on agricultural issues of Japan.
</P>
<P>
They and their counterparts from five Japanese universities and
a national agricultural research institute will hold discussions
on post-war agricultural development of Japan during the three-day
event, which opened at Fudan University in Shanghai today.
</P>
<P>
More than 200 experts from two countries submitted some 120
articles for discussion and academic exchanges.
</P>
<P>
The topics covered Japan's agricultural policies, problems of
grain, distribution system of agricultural products, farming
labor, environmental protection, and urban-rural relations.
</P>
<P>
Chinese experts, from the Ministry of Agriculture, the Chinese
Academy of Social Sciences, and four universities, said they would
draw lessons from and use the experiences of the modernization
drive of Japan's agricultural sector.  
</P>
