<HEADLINE> African First Ladies Summit to Open in Nigeria: </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, April 30 (Xinhua) -- The Organization of African
Unity (OAU) today announced that African first ladies will meet
in Abuja, capital of Nigeria from May 5 to 7 this year.
</P>
<P>
The announcement was made at a press conference held at the
OAU headquarters in the Ethiopian capital.
</P>
<P>
The first ever African first ladies summit, with the theme
of "peace and humanitarian issues focusing on the consequences of
conflict", will be organized under the auspices of the Nigerian
government with the collaboration of the OAU and the United
Nations Economic Commission for Africa (ECA).
</P>
<P>
The first ladies summit, endorsed by the OAU 65th session of
Council of Ministers in Tripoli last February after a submission
by the Nigerian delegation and the OAU secretariat, will be a
follow-up to the fourth World Conference on Women in Beijing,
China.
</P>
<P>
According to Nigerian diplomats here, Nigeria has sent
invitations to 15 countries and 13 first ladies are expected to
attend the Abuja first ladies summit. Other countries will send
powerful women delegations to the summit, they said. 
</P>
