<HEADLINE> Injury Keeps Privalova from World Championships </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 30 (Xinhua) -- European double sprint champion
Irina Privalova has injured her leg and will not compete at the
Athens world championships in August, a Russian athletic
federation official said on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Privalova, 28, had undergone a muscle operation in her upper
leg more than a week ago, according to Vadim Zelichyonok, coach of
the Russian national team.
</P>
<P>
"It is a pity we failed to diagnose the muscle rupture
earlier. She will definitely miss the world championships in
August," he said.
</P>
<P>
Zelinchyonok said the team would be selected after trials in
the town of Tula, south of Moscow, from July 7-10. 
