<HEADLINE> Education, Training, Top Priority of Govt: S'pore PM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, April 30 (Xinhua) -- Education and workers training
will be a top priority in this term of government, Prime Minister
Goh Chok Tong said in his May Day Message today, calling on
Singaporeans to be alert to new dangers as the Singapore economy
matures.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister said the difference between successful
countries and the less successful will turn on how well countries
nurture and use their talent and skills.
</P>
<P>
"If we compete on the basis of numbers, Singapore will lose to
far bigger countries. But on the basis of quality, discipline and
efficiency, we can hold our own and make a living for ourselves,"
he said.
</P>
<P>
"We need not just individual, but also group performance. We
have to harness Singaporeans into a strong united force to compete
against other national teams," he stressed.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister said that one of Singapore's strengths is
its political stability. And as a result, investors can plan
long-term because Singapore is "rational and predictable" in its
approach to challenges.
</P>
<P>
He also said that if workers remain disciplined and
hardworking, continuously upgrade their skills and productivity,
and cooperate with employers as joint venture partners, Singapore
can sustain full employment and continue to earn higher wages.
</P>
</TEXT>
