<HEADLINE> Two Killed in Tajikistan Grenade Attack </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 30 (Xinhua) -- Two people were killed and 20
wounded today in a grenade attack plotted to assassinate Tajik
President Emomali Rakhmonov, the Itar-Tass news agency said.
</P>
<P>
Rakhmonov was wounded in the leg and his condition was stable,
his press secretary Zafar Saidov said.
</P>
<P>
The other injured in the attack in the northern city of
Khudjand included Chairman of the Leninabad region Kosim Kosomov
and his deputy Okil Okilov.
</P>
<P>
Two people were in serious condition, the news agency said.
</P>
<P>
The attacker, identified as 20-year-old Firdavs Dustboboyev,
hurled a grenade at the president when he was getting out of a car
at a theatre to attend the celebrations of the 65th anniversary of
Khudjand University.
</P>
<P>
The grenade landed near the leaders when they were only a few
steps from the entrance to the theatre.
</P>
<P>
Dustboboyev was arrested immediately after the incident.
</P>
</TEXT>
