<HEADLINE> Share Prices Rise on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, April 30 (Xinhua) -- Share prices reversed their
downward trend and rose on the Singapore market today with the
benchmark Straits Times Industrials Index gaining 14.06 points to
close at 2004.26.
</P>
<P>
Total market volume increased marginally to 103.52 million
units, valued at 340.41 million Singapore dollars (236.4 million
U.S. dollars). Advances overwhelmed declines by 239 to 57, while
325 other counters remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
The Singapore Telecom was the most actively traded stock as it
posted a turnover of 6.17 million units. It was followed by UIC
which had 5.67 million of its shares traded. The Hong Kong Land
was next with 3.52 million shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
Local car distributor Cycle &AMP; Carriage (C&AMP;C) and Samanda
Holdings shared the top spot on the gainers' list as each of them
rose 40 cents to finish at 14.8 and ten dollars respectively.
Asean Fund, City Developments warrant 98, and the Overseas Chinese
Banking Corporation (OCBC) increased 30 cents each to end at 16.3
U.S. dollars, 9.1 Singapore dollars, and 16.9 Singapore dollars
respectively. The Singapore Airlines (SIA) Foreign and the
Singapore Press Holdings (SPH) Foreign gained 30 cents each too to
close at 12.8 and 26.8 Singapore dollars respectively.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Creative 50 and Sea View led the losers as
each of them declined 50 cents to end at 19.5 and 12 Singapore
dollars respectively. Malaya Resources was 34 cents lower at 4.16
Singapore dollars, while Thai Prime Fund fell 20 cents to finish
at 9.9 dollars.  
</P>
