<HEADLINE> Profits of Bayer Up in First Quarter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, April 30 (Xinhua) -- The German chemical giant Bayer AG
today reported its pre-tax profits at 1.2 billion marks (697
million U.S. dollars) in the first quarter of this year, up five
percent over the same period of 1996.
</P>
<P>
Reports reaching here said that the Cologne-based company
enjoyed a 8.2 percent growth in its turnover in the first quarter
of this year, which reached 13.2 billion marks (7.8 billion
dollars).
</P>
<P>
Bayer is in efforts to bring its turnover this year to about 50
billion marks (29 billion dollars), as against the 48.6 billion
marks (28.5 billion dollars) in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Despite declining prices as a result of tough competition,
Bayer is hopeful that its profits this year would be at least kept
at the 1996 record of 2.7 billion marks (1.59 billion dollars).
</P>
