<HEADLINE> Australian Stocks Close Well Off Highs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, April 30 (Xinhua) -- The Australian share market
closed firmer but well off its earlier Wall Street-inspired highs,
dragged down by profit-takers in late trade.
</P>
<P>
The all ordinaries index closed 8.9 points higher at 2488.0,
well off its intra-day high of 2515.1.
</P>
<P>
"The day kicked off very strongly on the back of a strong
performance on Wall Street, but fell as profit-takers came into
the market in the afternoon," said Reynolds and Co. broker Peter
Struk.
</P>
<P>
The all resources index closed seven points firmer at 1395.2,
while the all industrials index ended 11.5 points up at 3906.3.
</P>
<P>
One of the biggest movers of the day was BHP, which topped
turnover with 11 million shares traded, worth 200.6 million
Australian dollars (156.5 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Struk said BHP's strength continued to be driven by Tuesday's
announcement of a restructuring of its steel division, including
the closure of its Newcastle steel plant.
</P>
<P>
The banking sector recorded another strong day, rising 28.4
points to 4349.3.
</P>
<P>
National turnover totaled 390.9 million shares traded, valued
at 1.14 billion Australian dollars (889 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
