<HEADLINE> ADB Approves Loan to Micronesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, April 30 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Development Bank (ADB)
today approved an 18 million U.S. dollar loan to the Federated
States of Micronesia to assist its public sector reform program.
</P>
<P>
To address the overwhelming size of its public sector and a low
level of productivity, Micronesia has embarked on a comprehensive
program of reform, the ADB said.
</P>
<P>
The ADB loan will support reduction in the Micronesian
government size through early retirement and privatization of
selected activities and will help stimulate the private sector
during the period.
</P>
<P>
The ADB said it will also provide two technical assistance
grants to the reform program.  
</P>
