<HEADLINE> URGENT: Tajik President Wounded in Grenade Attack </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 30 (Xinhua) -- Tajik President Emomali Rakhmonov
was wounded today when a grenade hurled by a young man exploded
near him, reports reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
Rakhmonov was rushed to a hospital with wounds in the leg. His
press secretary Zafar Saidov said that the president's life is not
in danger.
</P>
<P>
