<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Prepares for Severer Floods in Yangtze </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 30 (Xinhua) -- China is making unprecedented
efforts to strengthen dams and dykes along the Yangtze River and
its branches, following estimates that a severe flood is likely to
strike the river this year.
</P>
<P>
Since March, the State Anti-Flood and Drought Headquarters has
sent 12 expert teams to local areas to inspect the preparation
work.
</P>
<P>
Experts from the Yangtze River Water Resources Commission said
that after two consecutive years of floods in the middle and lower
reaches of the Yangtze, a bigger flood is imminent this year and
this time, floods could even occur in the upper reaches.
</P>
<P>
Major flooding in the upper reaches of the river has not
occurred since 1981. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
