<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> ADB Invests in Venture Capital Fund for Pacific </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, April 30 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Development Bank (ADB)
today approved an equity investment of 3 million U.S. dollars in a
venture capital fund aimed at developing the private sector in the
small countries in the Pacific.
</P>
<P>
This is the first such fund targeted at these island nations,
the Manila-based ADB said.
</P>
<P>
The ADB said economic growth in these countries vitally needs
the private sector, but an acute shortage of equity or risk
capital has affected the sector's development.
</P>
<P>
The generally small size of potential private sector projects
in the Pacific region has constrained the bank's own efforts in
lending directly to such projects, the bank said.
</P>
<P>
The investments will be closed for redemption for ten years,
with a provision for extending the period for another two, it
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
