<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pakistani President Meets Chinese Well-Known Figures </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 30 (Xinhua) -- Pakistani President Farooq Ahmed
Khan Leghari met here today with Chinese well-known figures from
foreign affairs, academic, and non-governmental organizations.
</P>
<P>
Leghari said that Pakistani-Chinese friendship has stood the
test of time, and that the two countries have had sucessful
cooperation in all areas.
</P>
<P>
Leghari said that Pakistan is willing to maintain and develop
its good neighborly relations with China, expressing the hope that
government officials, intellectuals, and businessmen of the two
countries will have more exchanges and cooperation, and that
bilateral friendly ties will continue to grow.
</P>
<P>
Leghari also briefed the Chinese on Pakistan's view on the
situation in South Asia and Afghanistan as well as its domestic
affairs.
</P>
<P>
Zhu Liang, vice-president of the Chinese Association for
International Understanding, told the Pakistani president that
China thanked Pakistan for its support to China on the issues of
Taiwan and human rights.
</P>
<P>
Zhu noted that China is willing to further its friendship and
relations of cooperations with Pakistan, and said he hopes that
people of all sectors of the two countries will expand exchanges
and enhance mutual understanding.
</P>
<P>
Among those present at the occasion were Chinese Vice-Foreign
Minister Tang Jiaxuan, President of the China Society for Human
Rights Studies Zhu Muzhi, Chairman of the China Institute for
International Strategic Studies Xu Xin, President of the Chinese
People's Association for Friendship with Foreign Countries Qi
Huaiyuan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
