<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pakistan Hopes for Closer Trade Ties with China: President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 30 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Pakistani President
Farooq Ahmed Khan Leghari said here today that his country is
eager to bolster its economic and trade ties with China.
</P>
<P>
In a meeting earlier today with Guo Dongpo, president of the
China Council for the Promotion of International Trade, Leghari
noted that bilateral trade volume is not commensurate with sound
bilateral political relations, so the two countries need to take
measures to advance their economic and trade relationship.
</P>
<P>
Leghari said he hopes that the two countries' businesses will
explore new ways to expand their cooperation, including setting up
joint ventures and investing in each other.
</P>
<P>
Guo said that the Chinese businesses will make their own
efforts to promote economic and trade cooperation between the two
countries, and expressed the belief that Leghari's current China
trip is sure to promote such cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Shortly after the meeting, Leghari and Guo, together with some
Chinese enterpreneurs, had breakfast, where the Pakistani
president briefed those attending on Pakistan's economic situation
and investment environment, and welcomed Chinese businessmen to
invest in Pakistan and cooperate with Pakistani partners.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
