<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tajik President Wounded in Grenade Attack </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 30 (Xinhua) -- Tajik President Emomali Rakhmonov
was wounded on Wednesday morning in an assassination attempt.
</P>
<P>
A man tossed a grenade at Rakhmonov, who was visiting the
northern city of Khodzhent, 200 kilometers (125 miles) north of
the capital Dushanbe, reported the Interfax news agency.
</P>
<P>
The incident happened when Rakhmonov was preparing to make a
speech to mark the 60th anniversary of the city's university.
</P>
<P>
He was rushed to hospital and now in a stable condition, the
agency said.
</P>
<P>
A "large number of people'' were injured and no deaths were
reported, it said.
</P>
<P>
A 21 year-old suspect was taken into custody in connection with
the assassination attempt. 
</P>
</TEXT>
