<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0900 GMT, April 30 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW -- Tajik President Emomali Rakhmonov was wounded on
Wednesday morning in an assassination attempt when a man tossed a
grenade at him in the northern city of Khodzhent, 200 kilometers
(125 miles) north of the capital Dushanbe.
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- The Israeli army today "drastically" eased the
closure on the West Bank and Gaza Strip, allowing tens of
thousands of Palestinian laborers to enter into Israel, Israel
Radio reported.
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- Chinese Vice Premier and Foreign Minister Qian
Qichen Tuesday held talks with senior U.S. officials on relations
between China and the United States.
</P>
<P>
TIRANA -- Most universities, middle and primary schools in
Albania Tuesday formally restored schooling after a two-month
suspension caused by a sweeping unrest in the country.
</P>
<P>
NEW DELHI -- India has conveyed to Pakistan its inability to
hold the next round of foreign secretary-level talks in the first
week of May due to logistical reasons," the Hindustan Times
reported today.
</P>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS -- United Nations Secretary-General Kofi Annan
Tuesday called on both leaders of the Greek and Turkish Cypriot
communities to work with him for an earlier end to the long
division in Cyprus. 
</P>
</TEXT>
