<HEADLINE> Iran Declares German, Danish Ambassadors Unwelcome </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, April 30 (Xinhua) -- Iranian foreign minister
declared here today that some European ambassadors, especially
German and Danish ambassadors, are Unwelcome in his country.
</P>
<P>
This is one of Iran's official responses made by Foreign
Minister Ali Akbar Velayati at a press conference to the
declaration of the European Union ministerial meeting in
Luxembourg Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Velayati said that Iran will response the European countries
with same the intensity but in opposite direction. The loser
would not be Iran but the Europeans.
</P>
<P>
He said "some European ambassadors are not welcome and
German Ambassador (Horst Beshmann) is one of them. He is not
welcome in Iran."
</P>
<P>
In a response to the statement by Danish foreign minister
about delay in sending his ambassador back to Tehran, Velayati
said, Denmark can take as much time as it needs.
</P>
<P>
"We are not in a hurry to receive their ambassadors. As
a matter of fact, he is not welcomed at all," he added.
</P>
<P>
Answering a question posed by Xinhua, the Iranian foreign
minister said, the outcome of the EU ministerial meeting is
predictable and term it as "political backwardness" of the
European countries.
</P>
<P>
He said that the EU declaration is also a slab on the
face of the United States since European countries refused to
join in U.S. economic sanction against Iran.
</P>
<P>
EU had announced yesterday that it suspends ministerial level
exchange and "critical dialog" with Iran in a protest against the
alleged involvement of Iranian leaders in the 1992 assassination
of four exiled Kurdish opposition leaders in a Berlin
restaurant. 
