<HEADLINE> Mozambique's Cahora Bassa to Supply Power to </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, April 30 (Xinhua) -- Mozambique's Cahora Bassa Power
Station, located in the northern Tete Province, is expected to
supply electric power to Zimbabwe and South Africa.
</P>
<P>
Deputy Energy Minister Gastigo Langa said at the end of a
two-day electricity sub-committee meeting of the Southern African
Development Community (SADC) in Maputo that the wire project of
the power station would be completed in the middle of this year.
</P>
<P>
Also to be completed is the wire system connecting Cahora
Bassa with South Africa which is currently under repairing by the
Mozambican workers.
</P>
<P>
Export of Cahora Bassa electric power to its two southern
African neighbors would earn Mozambique at least 70 million U.S.
Dollars each year, according to Langa.
</P>
<P>
The SADC electric meeting, which opened on Tuesday, was
attended by government officials and experts from all the
12 SADC member countries. 
</P>
