<HEADLINE> Strange Cow Disease Found in Eastern Uganda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, April 30 (Xinhua) -- A strange cow disease is
spreading in Mbale District, eastern Uganda, local newspaper the
Monitor reported today.
</P>
<P>
The infected cattle get feverish and die within four days, and
the dissect of the dead cow shows a swollen spleen and yellowed
intestines, said the report.
</P>
<P>
Local farmers never know such a disease. They claimed the
disease was brought into the country with cows imported by
traders.
</P>
<P>
But some local people blamed the disease on the lack of
restriction on livestock movement between sub-counties and
counties. Further research is still going on. 
</P>
</TEXT>
