<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-30 06:56 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Israel Further Eases Closure on West Bank, Gaza </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, April 30 (Xinhua) -- The Israeli army today
"drastically" eased the closure on the West Bank and Gaza Strip,
allowing tens of thousands of Palestinian laborers to enter into
Israel, Israel Radio reported.
</P>
<P>
Starting from this morning, 28,000 workers from the West Bank
and 27,000 from the Gaza Strip are to be let in to their jobs in
the Jewish state. They must be married, over 29, and have a
security clearance, an army source said.
</P>
<P>
Israeli Defense Minister Yitzhak Mordechai told Israel Radio
that some restrictions was already lifted Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
"We will reach a stage where life will become very
reasonable, with no closure, although we will increase our
security activities," Mordechai said.
</P>
<P>
He was optimistic that ways would be found to enable
continuation of peace talks with the Palestinians, although he
stressed that this would not happen without a crackdown by the
Palestinian National Authority (PNA) on terror and those who
supported it.
</P>
<P>
"There will not be a closure, but we will increase our
security activity and if the Palestinians also do everything
that is necessary against terrorists, there will definitely be a
different atmosphere to the continuation of the (peace)
process," he said.
</P>
<P>
Israel started easing the closure Tuesday by allowing some
5,000 Palestinian merchants, who are married and over 30, to
enter into the Jewish country, and travel permits were also being
given to 650 PNA officials.
</P>
<P>
In addition, Palestinian hotel workers, medical personnel,
teachers, journalists, and employees of the Israeli Civil
Administration, international organizations and religious
institutions may also travel to Jerusalem from the West Bank.
</P>
<P>
Last month, Israel imposed the total closure on the West Bank
and Gaza Strip immediately after a suicide bombing attack in a
downtown coffee shop in Tel Aviv, which left three Israeli women
dead and over 50 other people injured.
</P>
<P>
The closure has barred tens of thousands of Palestinians from
returning to their jobs inside Israel, and from traveling
between the West Bank and Gaza Strip. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
