<HEADLINE> New University in Southern China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, April 30 (Xinhua) -- The largest university in an
ethnic minority area in China has been established in the Guangxi
Zhuang Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
Guangxi University was made by combining the previous Guangxi
University and Guangxi Agricultural University. It covers a 300-ha
area and accommodates 17,000 students.
</P>
<P>
It has more than 1,600 teachers and 191 postgraduates and
doctoral student advisors. It has 36 majors for postgraduates and
73 for undergraduates.
</P>
<P>
The new university expands the regions fields of learning and
is expected to provide better research and teaching conditions and
to produce more talented professionals for ethnic areas,
especially for Guangxi, university sources say. 
</P>
