<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UNESCO Boss Meets Zimbabwean President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, April 30 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Director-general of the
United Nations Educational, Scientific and Cultural Organization
(UNESCO) Federico Mayor last night held talks with Zimbabwean
President Robert Mugabe on cultural issues.
</P>
<P>
Mayor, who was in the country on a one-day official visit,
discussed with Mugabe ways to improve film production and the
promotion of art in general.
</P>
<P>
The two also addressed the issue of handicraft and cultural
promotion and how this could be developed to improve the lives of
rural women and help promote cultural integration.
</P>
<P>
"We looked into how we could encourage and promote the
development of handicraft. So that it benefits rural women. A
specialist in the area of cultural tourism would be engaged to
come up with a draft plan on how this should be done," Mayor
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
