<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Qian Qichen Meets Senior U.S. Officials, Lawmakers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 29 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice Premier and
Foreign Minister Qian Qichen today held talks with senior
U.S. officials on relations between China and the United States.
</P>
<P>
In his meeting with U.S. Treasury Secretary Robert Rubin, Qian
said that he hoped those man-made restrictions affecting the
normal development of Sino-U.S. trade ties be removed, so that
China could import more U.S. goods as it has great potentialities
to do so.
</P>
<P>
Qian also said that the annual review of the most-favored-nation
(MFN) trade status for China is one of the problems that affects
the trade and economic relations between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Rubin said that the United States has become aware of the
importance of the settlement of the MFN issue and China's entry
into the World Trade Organization.
</P>
<P>
During his talks with Defense Secretary William Cohen at
Pentagon, Qian said that the Sino-U.S. military exchanges have
made headway over the latter half of last year.
</P>
<P>
Cohen said that the United States upholds the policy of
engagement instead of containment toward China and he expected
there would be a prosperous and stable China emerging in the world.
</P>
<P>
Qian also met several U.S. lawmakers, including House speaker
Newt Gingrich and William Roth, chairman of Senate Committee of
Finance, and explained to them China's policies on Hong Kong,
Taiwan, nuclear non-proliferations and the entry into the World
Trade Organization.
</P>
<P>
Gingrich and other U.S. lawmakers, recalling their visits to
China earlier this year, said they were impressed by the progress
China has made in its economic reforms and they hoped to
strengthen the ties between the U.S. Congress and China's National
People's Congress.
</P>
<P>
They said that they appreciated Qian's explanation of China's
policies, which they said could help them know and understand more
and deeper about China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
