<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China To Issue Year's Third Round of Government Bonds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 30 (Xinhua) -- China will issue another 40
billion yuan (about 4.8 billion Us dollars) in State treasury
bonds in the month of May.
</P>
<P>
These are the first unregistered bonds this year and will be in
100-yuan, 1,000-yuan, and 5,000-yuan amounts with an annual coupon
rate of 9.18 percent. They can be traded immediately after the
issue closes.
</P>
<P>
They will be available in all state-owned and non-state-owned
commercial banks, urban cooperative banks, some rural credit
cooperatives, in outlets run by the Finance Ministry, or through
primary dealers, the ministry says.
</P>
<P>
China's annual treasury bond issue has grown rapidly in recent
years, and was more than 195 billion yuan last year. Government
bonds this year are budgeted at 248.5 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The first group of treasury bonds, valued at 20 billion yuan,
was issued between January 22 and February 17, and the second, 123
billion yuan in certificate bonds, came out in March. The issue
will end on October 20. 
</P>
</TEXT>
