<HEADLINE> Listed Companies Report Better Performance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 30 (Xinhua) -- Companies listed on the Shenzhen
stock market in south China have just released their annual
reports and generally reflect improved performances, according to
the Shenzhen Stock Exchange (SSE).
</P>
<P>
Of the 281 companies listed, 265 have released their yearly
financial reports in newspapers. There was an average per share
yield of 0.316 yuan, up 26.4 percent from the previous year,
according to the SSE.
</P>
<P>
Ninety-four of the firms had a per-share yield of 0.40 yuan or
more, up from 68 in 1995.
</P>
<P>
Blue chips maintained strong growth last year, and newly-listed
companies injected some new life into the stock market with
promising performances, said the SSE.
</P>
<P>
The SSE is doing its annual study of the yearly reports for
final verification, according to the exchange. 
</P>
