<HEADLINE> CIS States Report Mixed Economic Performance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 29 (Xinhua) -- A statistics committee of the
Commonwealth of Independent States (CIS) today reported mixed economic
performance among member states in the first quarter of the year.
</P>
<P>
A report released by the CIS's Inter-States Statistics
Committee said Georgia and Belarus saw increases of 10.9 percent
and 9.8 percent in their industrial output of the first three
months respectively, compared with the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
Kyrgyzstan, Uzbekistan and Kazakhstan reported increases of 6.9
and 4.2 percent, followed by Russia with 0.7 percent and Azerbaijan
0.4 percent.
</P>
<P>
But in Moldova, Tajikistan and Ukraine, the industrial output
dropped sharply by 14.9 percent, 14.5 percent and 6 percent
respectively.
</P>
<P>
The gross domestic product (GDP) of Belarus in the first quarter
increased by 9 percent. The growth rate was 3.5 in Azerbaijan, 1.7
percent in Uzbekistan, 0.2 percent in Russia and 0.1 percent in
Kyrgyzstan.
</P>
<P>
In Tajikistan and Armenia, the GDP grew by 4.7 percent and 1.4
percent respectively in the first two months over the same period
last year, while in Ukraine and Turkmenistan the GDP was down 8.9
percent and 2.4 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
