<HEADLINE> Italian Mafia Boss Arrested After Four Years at Large </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, April 29 (Xinhua) -- Italian police arrested a Mafia boss
today in Calabria, in southern Italy, after he was at large for
four years.
</P>
<P>
Giuseppe Mancuso, described by the Italian Interior Ministry as
one of the 30 most dangerous criminals in the country, was the
head of the Calabrian mafia and was arrested early this morning
when police raided the house where he was staying in a village.
</P>
<P>
Mancuso, 48, was charged with ordering at least five murders in
the period of 1980-1990 and playing a key role in arms and drug
traffickings. 
