<HEADLINE> India Unable to Hold Talks with Pakistan in Early May </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, April 30 (Xinhua) -- India has conveyed to Pakistan
its inability to hold the next round of foreign secretary-level
talks in the first week of May due to logistical reasons," the
Hindustan Times reported today.
</P>
<P>
"We hope to finalize mutually convenient dates for the talks
soon," an External Affairs Ministry spokesman said here on
Tuesday.
