on all outstanding issues between the two countries would be
worked out during the summit of the South Asian Association for
Regional Cooperation (SAARC) in Maldives from May 12 to 14 where
Indian Prime Minister I.K. Gujral and his Pakistani counterpart
Nawaz Sharif are expected to meet, the spokesman said.  
