<HEADLINE> Dhaka Stock Exchange Council to Be Dissolved </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, April 30 (Xinhua) -- The Bangladeshi government has
decided to dissolve the Dhaka Stock Exchange (DSE) Council in a
bid to restore the investors' confidence on the capital market,
according to competent sources.
</P>
<P>
a high-level meeting, attended by the officials of the Finance
Ministry and the Securities and Exchange Commission, was held on
Tuesday and the meeting felt that the dissolution of the DSE
Council was an urgent need to help stabilize the capital market.
</P>
<P>
The present 11-member DSE Council was elected in 1995 by the
DSE members. Among the 11 members of the council, four including
the present DSE chairman Imtiaz Hossain were charged with
manipulating share prices during the last five months of the past
year.
</P>
<P>
The biggest-ever stock market scandal heavily hit the market
and dragged the benchmark index to a free fall.
</P>
<P>
On the other hand, Kerb market traders on Tuesday continued
their demonstrations in front of the DSE building, demanding the
dissolution of the DSE Council.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the DSE all share prices index rose on Tuesday after
witnessing massive fall for last few days. The index advanced to
935.52 points from 899.38 of the previous day, registering a 36.14
points rise.
</P>
<P>
The market capitalization also increased to 77.87 billion taka
(about 1.94 billion U.S. dollars) from Monday's 74.86 billion taka
(about 1.87 billion dollars).  
</P>
</TEXT>
