<HEADLINE> Indonesia Launches V-Sat Village Telecom Service </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, April 30 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia's state
telecommunications company Pt. Telkom and its partner Pt. Bukaka
Singapore Telecom International (BSI) Tuesday launched a service
called 'Kbu-v-sat' (village public phone booth via satellite) in
Indonesia's South Sulawesi province.
</P>
<P>
Pt. Telkom and BSI are slated until July 1997 to install the
booths in about 170 sub-districts of the 10 provinces in the
eastern part of Indonesia, according to reports reaching here
today.
</P>
<P>
The launching of the Kbu-v-sat was marked by a long distance
call using the new facility between an official of the local
telecommunication office in Sorong (Irian Jaya), and the head of
local telecommunication office in Ujungpandang, South Sulawesi.
</P>
<P>
The new service aims to help facilitate the vote counting in
the general election on May 29, an official of Pt. Telkom said.
</P>
<P>
Until 2004, the end of the Seventh Five-Year Development, it is
expected that all villages in the region will have the new
facility, the official added.  
</P>
