<HEADLINE> Russia's Foreign Trade Drops Slightly in First Quarter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 29 (Xinhua) -- Russia's foreign trade totaled
34.5 billion U.S. dollars in the first quarter of this year, 1
percent lower than the same period last year, the State Statistics
Committee said today.
</P>
<P>
Exports rose 3 percent to 20.8 billion dollars, while imports
dropped 6 percent to 13.7 billion dollars, resulting in a surplus
of 7.1 billion dollars or 29 percent over the figure a year before.
</P>
<P>
Trade with other former Soviet republics fell by 13 percent to
7.9 billion dollars from the same period last year. Exports and
imports dropped by 6 and 20 percent respectively to 4.3 and 3.6
billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
Trade with other countries went up by 3 percent to 26.6 billion
dollars, with a total export of 16.5 billion dollars and a total
import of 10.1 billion dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
