<HEADLINE> MD Aircraft Corp. Donates Computer Training System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, April 30 (Xinhua) -- The McDonnell Douglas Corp. of
the United States donated a computer base training (CBT) system to
a leading Chinese aviation college recently.
</P>
<P>
Composed of ten multi-media Pentium computers and three kinds
of training software, the system will be used to help the China
Civil Aviation Flying College to establish a CBT room for flying
McDonnell Douglas planes.
</P>
<P>
According to Andy Quinn, vice president of Product Support of
MD (China), the system which cost over one million US dollars for
software development, is designed for the new MD-11, MD-82, and
MD-90 aircrafts.
</P>
<P>
Based in Guanghan City, Sichuan Province, the college provides
90 percent of the pilots now flying on international and domestic
routes for Chinese airline companies. The college is currently
able to train over 1,500 students a year.
</P>
<P>
"The donation will play an important part on courses on the
theory and practice of flying MD aircrafts scheduled soon", said
Wang Shixiang, president of the college. 
