<HEADLINE> Express Way For Northeast China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, April 30 (Xinhua) -- Northeast China's Liaoning
Province plans to spend 10 billion yuan on an expressway that will
link the provincial capital of Shenyang with Shanhaiguan, the
easternmost part of the Great Wall.
</P>
<P>
Construction of the 361-km express way, which will have a speed
limit of 120 kph, will begin in May and is expected to be
completed in the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
The road is a section of the expressway from Shenyang to
Beijing that will be the longest six-lane highway in the country.
</P>
<P>
The cost will be partly covered by a 200 million US dollar loan
from the Asian Development Bank.
</P>
<P>
Liaoning has 570 km of expressways, of which the
Shenyang-Dalian section, at 375 km, is the longest in the
country. 
</P>
