<HEADLINE> Cambodian Politicians, Army Leaders Meet for Stability </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, April 29 (Xinhua) -- Cambodian politicians and army
leaders today met and decided to take measures to avoid military
conflict and keep national stability.
</P>
<P>
More than 700 representatives, including cabinet ministers,
state secretaries, leading members of provinces and cities as well
as all the senior army officers attended the meeting, which was
hosted by the mixed coordination committee of the ruling FUNCINPEC
Party and the Cambodian People's Party.
</P>
<P>
According to a statement issued after the meeting, Cambodia has
made great achievements in national reconciliation and economic
construction since the government was formed four years ago.
</P>
<P>
However, "the current situation of Cambodia had not only
worried us, but also caused great concerns of the international
community," the statement said, adding that it had seriously
affected the country's stability and economic development.
</P>
<P>
Therefore, Co-Prime Ministers Norodom Ranariddh and Hun Sen
agreed to try to stablize the country's situation and resolutely
avoid any military conflict, it said.
</P>
<P>
The statement required all the armed forces to keep neutral,
stay away from party strifes and keep political and social
stability so as to guarantee the coming national elections.
</P>
<P>
The tense situation in Cambodia has begun to ease after the
meeting, according to local media. 
</P>
</TEXT>
